# Amazon EKS

## When ECS isn't enough → EKS

- **Existing Kubernetes** investment — one operational model
- **Multi-cloud / on-prem** portability (manifests are portable; task defs aren't)
- Rich **K8s features** — taints, controllers, Helm, meshes, GitOps

## What EKS manages

The **control plane** (API server, etcd, scheduler) — managed, ~**$0.10/hr per cluster**. You own **worker nodes**:

- **Managed Node Group** — AWS runs the EC2 lifecycle — the default
- **Self-Managed** — your AMI / ASG (Windows, custom kernel)
- **Fargate Profile** — no EC2 (no DaemonSets / privileged / EBS / GPU)

**Default: ECS on Fargate.** EKS when K8s is a **requirement, not a preference**.
